'''Llisan Al-Ɣarbi''' (isnamk "'''Tutlayt n utaram'''") iga ism lli ittyufkan i yat tutlayt tamaziɣt inɣuban. Tutlayt ad tkka tt inn ar sis sawln ɣ umata n izaɣarn iṭlanṭiyn n [[Lmɣrib]]<ref>B. Frankel, [https://books.google.fr/books?id=CDYsAQAAIAAJ History in Dispute: The Middle East since 1945. First series] (St. James Press, 2003), p.206</ref><ref name=":0">[https://books.google.fr/books?id=IXUPAQAAMAAJ Awal, Numéros 19 à 21] (Maison des sciences de l'homme, 1999), p.157</ref>, yili mad ttinin mas [[Tutlayt Taclḥit|Tclḥit]] tutlayt as akkʷ yaẓn<ref name=":0" />.

Llisan Al-Ɣarbi ikka t inn iga tutlayt tamaddut n umqqun n [[burɣwaṭa]], ig tutlayt lli issmrs [[Ṣaliḥ Ibn Ṭaṛif]] ɣ "lqqʷṛan Amaziɣ" nns.

Tiṛẓi n [[Buṛɣwaṭa]] mgal [[Imwaḥḥidn|Imuwaḥḥidn]] ɣ tasuta tiss 11, azwag n mnnawt tqbilin tiɛṛabin d tiznatiyin s umnid s ifassn n [[Imwaḥḥidn|Imuwaḥḥidn]] d [[Imarinen|Imariniyn]], anbaz n iburtuɣaliyn ɣ tasuta tiss 15, d mnnaw n id buhyyuf tga tyafut-nnsn asmatti n imzdaɣ d ussimẓi n uṭṭun n imṣmuḍn; issaɣ akkʷ aylli yad ittubdarn s usɛṛṛb n aylli d iqqaman ɣ imzdaɣn imṣmuḍn d tmttant n Llisan Al-Ɣarbi.

Ass-a, mnnawt tqbilin d iɣsan n imṣmudn nna isuln gr [[Dukkala]], [[Ccawiya]], [[Zɛir]] d [[Iregragn]], maccan ar akkʷ sawaln taɛṛabt.

